chunk_content: The correct number can be determined by recreating the reported S number using patient records and registries (see subsection 3.3, Step 3: site-level assessment for details). People who simultaneously seek care at more than one facility. The number of people receiving treatment can be incorrectly counted if people are simultaneously registered at and considered to be receiving treatment by two facilities. This error will always result in over-counting the number of people receiving treatment. The correct number can be determined by comparing electronic records, where available, across facilities, reviewing possible matches to determine whether they are the same person, and then assigning a single location for counting purposes.
